WEBVTT

00:05.634 --> 00:06.733
Hey, Sean,
spot me, buddy.

00:06.768 --> 00:08.167
Yeah, Yeah.
Jesus Christ, look at you.

00:08.202 --> 00:10.596
What, you been working out like crazy?
What's going on?

00:10.634 --> 00:12.234
Well, firefighter calendar
shoots next week.

00:12.269 --> 00:13.385
You're doing
that thing again?

00:13.420 --> 00:14.466
Yeah.
Fourth year in a row.

00:14.501 --> 00:17.401
They want me so bad,
they let me pick my own month.

00:17.436 --> 00:18.868
- Really?
- Yeah.

00:18.903 --> 00:20.265
I don't know, man.

00:20.300 --> 00:21.501
That always seemed
a little gay.

00:21.536 --> 00:22.699
What? Are you kidding?

00:22.734 --> 00:24.467
You get one month
in that calendar,

00:24.502 --> 00:26.200
you're looking
at a whole year of ass.

00:26.235 --> 00:27.499
Come on.

00:27.534 --> 00:29.334
I'm telling you.
They come at me in waves.

00:29.369 --> 00:31.900
So you think I can get in it?

00:31.935 --> 00:33.084
Into what, the calendar?

00:33.119 --> 00:34.199
You just said it was gay.

00:34.234 --> 00:36.350
Well, yeah, but maybe it's gay
in a good way.

00:36.385 --> 00:38.467
Yeah, the kind of gay
that gets you straight sex.

00:38.502 --> 00:39.666
Yeah, it is.

00:39.701 --> 00:42.300
I'll put in a good word.
Little late in the day,

00:42.335 --> 00:43.701
but I'll see
what I can do.

00:43.736 --> 00:44.666
Whatever.
No big deal.

00:44.701 --> 00:46.234
- Hey, you guys see Tommy yet?
- No.

00:46.269 --> 00:47.632
Not yet, chief.

00:47.667 --> 00:49.801
Maybe he's outside
talking to another dead girl.

00:49.836 --> 00:51.165
Excuse me?

00:51.200 --> 00:53.200
What, I'm the only one
that thought that was weird?

00:53.235 --> 00:54.951
Yeah, come on, chief.
It was a little creepy.

00:54.986 --> 00:57.060
You don't think
Tommy's cracking up a bit?

00:57.095 --> 00:59.134
Listen, you two,
that was one incident.

00:59.169 --> 01:00.165
Look, chief--

01:00.200 --> 01:01.667
I got nothing but love
for Tommy.

01:01.702 --> 01:03.099
He's a great guy,
he's our brother,

01:03.134 --> 01:05.033
but that does nothing
to change the fact

01:05.068 --> 01:06.933
that he had a very long,
very animated chat

01:06.968 --> 01:08.232
with a very dead little girl.

01:08.267 --> 01:10.534
It doesn't take a shrink,
you know what I'm saying?

01:10.569 --> 01:12.651
And that's none of
your business, Rivera, huh?

01:12.686 --> 01:14.699
Yeah, okay. Well, uh,
how about when he flips out

01:14.734 --> 01:17.401
in the middle of our next
big fire, and I wind up dead?

01:17.436 --> 01:18.267
Is it my business then?

01:22.367 --> 01:24.200
Just tell him
I was looking for him, huh?

01:24.235 --> 01:26.998
Yeah, all right, chief.

01:27.029 --> 01:28.818
Jesus, I don't want
to be an asshole, but--

01:28.869 --> 01:31.401
Hey, look, don't sweat it.
I get it.

01:31.494 --> 01:33.268
- Let's go again, yeah?
- Yeah.

01:34.000 --> 01:36.200
Tour starts at 9:00, Tommy,
not quarter to 10.

01:36.235 --> 01:37.165
I'm sorry, man.

01:37.200 --> 01:38.833
This isn't about you and me.

01:38.868 --> 01:41.234
George had to be at
his kids' school this morning.

01:41.269 --> 01:43.601
He hung on for 45 minutes,
but you didn't even call.

01:43.636 --> 01:45.200
I'm sorry. It won't
happen again, man.

01:45.235 --> 01:46.532
Okay? I'm sorry.

01:46.567 --> 01:48.232
What's going on
with you?

01:48.267 --> 01:50.484
I just-- Uh... I need
more vacation time.

01:50.519 --> 01:52.701
I already ate my regular
vacation days up.

01:52.748 --> 01:53.545
I-- I don't know.

01:53.589 --> 01:55.349
Do you ever think
about going downtown?

01:55.402 --> 01:56.566
What do you mean?

01:56.601 --> 01:57.766
There's a guy downtown.

01:57.801 --> 01:59.467
He's some sort
of a shrink, I guess.

01:59.502 --> 02:00.666
You go down and tell him

02:00.701 --> 02:02.501
you feel a little shaky,
about to crack up,

02:02.536 --> 02:03.632
boom, two weeks.

02:03.667 --> 02:04.917
- Two weeks? Wow.
- Yeah.

02:04.952 --> 02:06.132
I mean, I did it myself.

02:06.167 --> 02:08.632
- You were feeling a little, uh--?
- No, no, no.

02:08.667 --> 02:10.868
My wife wanted to go on some
New England foliage thing,

02:10.902 --> 02:12.432
you know, with the leaves
and that shit.

02:12.467 --> 02:15.100
It was the only way
I could get the time off.

02:15.135 --> 02:16.801
What would I say, you know?

02:16.836 --> 02:18.199
You make something up.

02:18.234 --> 02:20.267
I mean, you go down there
and tell him you--

02:20.302 --> 02:22.067
You can't sleep,
you got the shakes.

02:22.102 --> 02:23.132
Right.

02:23.167 --> 02:24.768
I mean, what's the worst
that can happen?

02:24.803 --> 02:26.132
Even if you don't
get time off,

02:26.167 --> 02:27.768
at least you get
to talk to somebody,

02:27.803 --> 02:29.602
if you need to
talk to somebody.

02:29.637 --> 02:31.401
Who says I need
to talk to somebody?

02:31.436 --> 02:32.499
I'm just saying...

02:32.534 --> 02:34.801
If you need to talk to somebody.

02:36.167 --> 02:37.167
I'll think about it.

02:37.202 --> 02:38.668
Thanks.

02:38.703 --> 02:40.134
Yeah.

