02:51.129 --> 02:54.329
BUTTERFLY

03:36.401 --> 03:37.467
Jesus.

03:37.502 --> 03:38.499
Hey.

03:38.534 --> 03:39.734
- Whoa, whoa.
- I'm sorry.

03:39.769 --> 03:40.834
Hey, Steve.

03:40.869 --> 03:41.865
Hey, Tommy.

03:41.900 --> 03:42.998
What's going on,
man?

03:43.033 --> 03:44.234
Not much, man. I'm just working.

03:44.269 --> 03:45.432
- How you been?
- Pretty good.

03:45.467 --> 03:46.965
- Oh, you're down here now.
- Yeah.

03:47.000 --> 03:50.134
Wow. I barely even recognized
you in the suit and the tie.

03:50.169 --> 03:52.567
Yeah, I thought I was gonna
get out of the department

03:52.602 --> 03:54.667
after my accident,
but no such luck, you know?

03:54.702 --> 03:56.932
They hooked me back in.
Desk job.

03:56.967 --> 03:59.100
Putting out different kinds
of fires now.

03:59.135 --> 04:01.134
- Yeah.
- What you doing down here?

04:01.169 --> 04:02.632
Um...

04:02.667 --> 04:04.733
I'm, uh... Me and the guys--

04:04.768 --> 04:06.634
You remember Vito Costello
from my house?

04:06.669 --> 04:07.699
- Died 9/11.
- Yeah.

04:07.734 --> 04:09.332
Me and the guys are, uh--

04:09.367 --> 04:11.801
We're trying to get a, uh,
a jogging path named after him.

04:11.836 --> 04:13.768
- Yeah, I remember Vito.
- Yeah.

04:13.803 --> 04:15.701
He was--
He was a huge jogger.

04:15.736 --> 04:17.199
Well, listen, uh...

04:17.233 --> 04:19.834
why don't you give it to me?
I'll just push it right through.

04:19.869 --> 04:22.434
Well, the thing is, I promised
his-- His widow that--

04:22.469 --> 04:23.466
It's no problem.

04:23.501 --> 04:25.100
I can push it
right through for you.

04:25.135 --> 04:26.200
I'll push it right through--

04:26.235 --> 04:27.566
Hey, Tommy.

04:27.601 --> 04:28.699
How you doing, man?

04:28.734 --> 04:30.617
- Good to see you.
- What's going on?

04:30.652 --> 04:32.466
This is a health form,
Tommy.

04:32.501 --> 04:34.734
You know what? The guys knew
I was coming down--

04:34.769 --> 04:36.132
it's like a joke.

04:36.167 --> 04:38.667
Oh, listen, it's no problem.
I don't need a petition.

04:38.702 --> 04:40.667
I'll push it through
by the end of the week.

04:40.702 --> 04:41.733
Yeah?

04:41.768 --> 04:43.467
That'd be great.
That'd be huge.

04:43.502 --> 04:44.833
Hey, it's for Vito, right?

04:44.868 --> 04:46.334
- That's right.
- I'll take care of it.

04:46.369 --> 04:47.918
- I'll call you.
- Thanks, man.

04:47.953 --> 04:49.467
All right.
Take it easy, Tommy.

04:49.502 --> 04:50.467
- Thanks.
- All right.

04:50.502 --> 04:51.367
See you.

05:02.900 --> 05:03.933
Next!

05:12.667 --> 05:13.534
Next!

05:16.501 --> 05:18.250
- Gavin, 62nd truck.
- Ahem. Yeah.

05:18.285 --> 05:20.000
What seems to be the problem?

05:20.035 --> 05:21.766
Well, uh--

05:21.801 --> 05:24.501
been, uh... Been having
some trouble sleeping.

05:24.536 --> 05:26.332
That's it?

05:26.367 --> 05:28.783
Um, some other, uh...

05:28.818 --> 05:31.200
you know, kind of...

05:31.235 --> 05:32.900
Shh. Gotcha.

05:36.467 --> 05:37.865
I think you're okay
for full duty.

05:37.900 --> 05:40.433
Just take these,
check back with me in a month.

05:40.468 --> 05:42.967
Direction and dosages
will be on the bottle.

05:47.501 --> 05:49.199
That-- That's it?

05:49.234 --> 05:51.734
You want to talk or something?

05:54.267 --> 05:55.232
No.

05:55.267 --> 05:58.265
Nah. No, I'm good.

05:58.300 --> 05:59.734
You're not seeing dead people,
are you?

05:59.769 --> 06:02.499
No.

06:02.534 --> 06:04.534
Because word's gotten out,
you see dead people,

06:04.569 --> 06:06.534
you're in for an automatic
two-week vacation.

06:06.569 --> 06:07.898
I got three, four guys a week

06:07.933 --> 06:10.100
coming in here
seeing dead people.

06:10.135 --> 06:11.399
I-- I--

06:11.434 --> 06:13.734
I just thought maybe I could
use, you know...

06:13.769 --> 06:14.933
A couple weeks off, that's all.

06:14.968 --> 06:16.932
Try the pills first.

06:16.967 --> 06:19.432
Okay. Um, here's the thing.

06:19.467 --> 06:22.634
I can't, uh...
I can't really read these.

06:22.669 --> 06:24.100
You can't sleep, right?

06:24.135 --> 06:25.517
Right.

06:25.552 --> 06:26.909
Depressed?

06:26.944 --> 06:28.232
Uh, yeah.

06:28.267 --> 06:29.767
What's that one?

06:29.802 --> 06:31.267
Can't get it up?

06:31.302 --> 06:32.632
Oh, no, no.

06:32.667 --> 06:33.868
I don't have that problem.

06:33.903 --> 06:34.933
Oh, sorry.

06:36.467 --> 06:37.766
Okay.

06:37.801 --> 06:40.017
Well, you know...

06:40.052 --> 06:41.926
You never know.

06:41.961 --> 06:43.381
Thanks, doc.

06:43.416 --> 06:44.801
Hey, you drink?

06:44.836 --> 06:46.532
Um...

06:46.567 --> 06:47.799
not really.

06:47.834 --> 06:51.033
Well, don't take that stuff
with booze.

06:51.068 --> 06:52.134
It won't be good.

06:52.169 --> 06:53.901
Next!

06:53.936 --> 06:55.634
Okay.

07:10.900 --> 07:12.000
Hey, Rog.

07:13.401 --> 07:14.667
How's it going?

07:17.734 --> 07:19.132
Asshole.

07:19.167 --> 07:21.167
Look, I told you
I didn't want to see you.

07:21.202 --> 07:22.232
Why are you here?

07:22.267 --> 07:24.332
Because this is bullshit,
babe!

07:24.367 --> 07:25.932
Come on. We were
going along just fine.

07:25.967 --> 07:28.200
Until you had a bunch of friends
beat up my ex-husband.

07:28.235 --> 07:30.265
First of all,
I had nothing to do with that.

07:30.300 --> 07:32.701
And second, it wasn't a bunch,
it was... three guys.

07:32.736 --> 07:34.265
Hello.

07:34.300 --> 07:36.501
Oh, hey, sorry.
I didn't know you had company.

07:36.536 --> 07:37.499
He knew.

07:37.534 --> 07:38.932
He saw me pull up.

07:38.967 --> 07:41.167
You know what? I didn't
come to start a fight.

07:41.202 --> 07:42.132
What do you want?

07:42.167 --> 07:43.633
I got that part
for the sink.

07:43.668 --> 07:45.065
Wanted to make sure
it works.

07:45.100 --> 07:46.634
- Now's not a good time.
- Two seconds.

07:46.669 --> 07:48.001
Oh, you're so innocent.

07:48.036 --> 07:49.299
- Mr. Nice Guy.
- What?

07:49.334 --> 07:51.801
Tell her about what you
did to me in the kitchen.

07:51.836 --> 07:53.200
About holding my head
over the stove.

07:53.235 --> 07:54.432
- What?!
- Yeah.

07:54.467 --> 07:56.199
You put his head over the stove?

07:56.234 --> 07:57.801
I don't remember
that particular detail.

07:57.836 --> 07:59.033
- Oh, please.
- Hey, Mom.

07:59.068 --> 08:00.534
- Hey, Dad.
- Hey.

08:00.569 --> 08:01.868
Can I get a drink?

08:01.903 --> 08:03.132
Sure. Go ahead.

08:03.167 --> 08:04.432
You know,
Connor was there.

08:04.464 --> 08:06.473
He probably remembers exactly
what happened, right, son?

08:06.515 --> 08:08.723
Yeah. You mean when
you and Roger were fighting?

08:08.769 --> 08:09.898
Right.

08:09.933 --> 08:11.900
Tell your mother, um,
who hit who first.

08:16.234 --> 08:18.000
Roger threw the first punch.

08:18.035 --> 08:19.232
There you go.

08:19.267 --> 08:20.350
What?
That's bullshit.

08:20.385 --> 08:21.826
Roger, watch your language.

08:21.861 --> 08:23.614
Yeah, asshole.
Sorry. Sorry.

08:23.649 --> 08:25.332
I did not throw the first punch.

08:25.367 --> 08:27.900
Listen, I don't know what's
going on here, young man,

08:27.935 --> 08:29.701
but I suggest you tell
your mother right now

08:29.736 --> 08:30.667
what exactly
happened.

08:35.900 --> 08:37.200
Roger started it.

08:37.235 --> 08:38.466
See?
He's lying!

08:38.501 --> 08:40.933
You know what? Don't call
my kid a liar. Okay, pal?

08:40.967 --> 08:42.599
Okay, Tommy, just go.

08:42.634 --> 08:45.300
- You sure?
- Yes. I can handle this.

08:45.335 --> 08:46.265
Goodbye.

08:46.300 --> 08:48.234
- Thanks, pal.
- Nice teamwork.

08:49.701 --> 08:51.000
Okay, honey, just go.

08:52.777 --> 08:54.822
Lookit, I talked to
my ex-brother-in-law, Roger.

08:54.885 --> 08:56.909
He's a detective.
He told me you were involved.

08:56.949 --> 08:58.472
I think he knows
what he's talking about.

08:58.486 --> 08:58.947
Wake up.

08:58.968 --> 09:00.566
It's such bullshit!

09:00.601 --> 09:02.401
You want to know what's
really happening here?

09:02.436 --> 09:03.601
No! Could you just leave?

09:03.636 --> 09:04.834
No!
Listen to me!

09:06.033 --> 09:07.666
It's that asshole
across the street.

09:07.701 --> 09:09.501
Your ex-husband has been
trying to break us apart

09:09.536 --> 09:11.898
since day one.

09:11.933 --> 09:13.299
Just answer one question.

09:13.334 --> 09:14.734
And you better tell the truth,
Roger,

09:14.769 --> 09:16.401
because if you lie, I will know.

09:16.436 --> 09:18.032
Okay.

09:18.067 --> 09:21.768
Did you have anything to do with
those guys beating up Tommy?

09:21.803 --> 09:24.467
Define "anything."

09:28.667 --> 09:30.601
Hey.
Hey, I need you to cut it.

09:30.636 --> 09:31.699
Hey. Hey!

09:31.734 --> 09:33.100
What's the problem?

09:35.401 --> 09:36.501
Nothing. Never mind.

09:36.536 --> 09:37.466
Sorry.

09:37.501 --> 09:38.933
Hey, uh...
Bob Shinsky.

09:38.968 --> 09:39.967
Tom Gavin.

09:40.002 --> 09:40.932
How are you?

09:40.981 --> 09:43.237
- You're the firefighter, right?
- Yeah.

09:43.334 --> 09:45.601
It looks like you had a fire
of your own recently.

09:45.636 --> 09:46.799
It's kind of ironic.

09:46.834 --> 09:49.933
But I want you to know
I think it's great.

09:49.968 --> 09:51.366
Your work, uh, you know,

09:51.401 --> 09:54.000
it takes a lot of guts to handle
that job, and I'm impressed.

09:54.035 --> 09:55.099
Thank you.

09:55.134 --> 09:56.367
What-- What do you do?

09:56.402 --> 09:57.501
I'm a psychotherapist.

09:57.536 --> 09:58.601
Oh, you're a shrink?

09:58.636 --> 10:00.499
Guilty, yeah.

10:00.534 --> 10:02.601
That's funny.
You're the second one today.

10:02.636 --> 10:03.801
Hey, let me ask you something.

10:03.836 --> 10:04.766
I got these pills.

10:04.801 --> 10:06.265
Could you take
a look at these?

10:06.300 --> 10:09.534
Let me just put this
down for a second.

10:10.334 --> 10:12.134
Are these good?

10:13.768 --> 10:14.766
Oh, yeah.

10:14.801 --> 10:16.165
Well, these are all fine,
I guess.

10:16.200 --> 10:18.300
I mean... You know, they don't
work for everyone.

10:18.335 --> 10:19.299
Right.

10:19.334 --> 10:20.900
Now, would I take them
separately,

10:20.935 --> 10:22.265
or all at the same time?

10:22.300 --> 10:23.699
Well, I don't think you'd want

10:23.734 --> 10:25.933
to take all three of these
medications at the same time...

10:25.968 --> 10:27.898
- No?
- No, not unless you wanted to be

10:27.933 --> 10:29.983
a really sleepy, happy guy
with an erection.

10:30.018 --> 10:32.033
No, the erection thing,
that was a mistake.

10:32.068 --> 10:33.501
So these are good?

10:33.536 --> 10:34.766
Uh, I guess.

10:34.801 --> 10:36.300
I don't usually prescribe
anything

10:36.335 --> 10:37.632
unless it's a last resort.

10:37.667 --> 10:39.333
There are people
in my profession,

10:39.368 --> 10:41.301
- they hand out meds like candy.
- Yeah.

10:41.336 --> 10:43.199
I, uh... I think
talking one-on-one

10:43.234 --> 10:45.132
is much more effective
in the long term,

10:45.167 --> 10:47.868
so consider that before you dig
into your stash there.

10:47.903 --> 10:49.467
All right, thanks, doc.
Appreciate it.

10:49.502 --> 10:51.334
- Oh, thanks.
- See you around.

10:51.369 --> 10:52.632
Excuse me. I...

10:52.667 --> 10:55.434
I was admiring your deck
out back the other day,

10:55.469 --> 10:56.766
and I was--

10:56.801 --> 10:59.267
I'm actually thinking about
putting one on myself.

10:59.302 --> 11:00.399
Yeah. Yeah.

11:00.434 --> 11:01.699
So, uh, who did yours?

11:01.734 --> 11:03.768
I did.
Me and the guys from my crew.

11:03.803 --> 11:05.032
- Really?
- Yeah.

11:05.068 --> 11:07.293
What are you thinking of doing,
thinking of spending?

11:07.323 --> 11:08.406
I don't know.

11:08.434 --> 11:09.900
A thousand, maybe 1,500, but--

11:09.935 --> 11:10.865
Yeah.

11:10.900 --> 11:12.499
I don't know, man.

11:12.534 --> 11:14.701
It's just, you know--
Really taking a week's work

11:14.736 --> 11:17.000
and just compressing it
into two days.

11:17.035 --> 11:18.401
I'd have to
take a look at--

11:18.436 --> 11:19.366
17-- Maybe 2000.

11:19.401 --> 11:20.401
2000. That's more like it.

11:20.436 --> 11:21.666
- Really?
- Yeah.

11:21.701 --> 11:24.134
Let me talk to the guys,
and I'll get back to you.

11:24.169 --> 11:25.699
- I'm very serious.
- Okay. All right.

11:25.734 --> 11:28.134
Nice to talk to you, doc.
I'll get right back at you.

11:28.169 --> 11:29.751
So nice
to see you.

11:29.786 --> 11:31.299
Two grand for a porch?

11:31.334 --> 11:33.133
Last one we did,
we got what, 600 bucks?

11:33.168 --> 11:34.933
Who is this guy?
The king of chumps?

11:34.968 --> 11:36.165
Some shrink, you know?

11:36.221 --> 11:37.966
I figure we'd get
Charlie Walsh's cousin

11:38.008 --> 11:40.433
to get the lumber for 300 bones,
divide the rest up.

11:40.477 --> 11:41.259
You in?

11:41.296 --> 11:43.029
